<br>
People just don't get it by fleeing half the zone, with a mob on your tail this is the chain reaction of what happens: <br>
<br>
1.  You hit any groups on the way to zone or they get groups on their way back from zone<br>
2.  If you reach the zone, there is likely a few MDKs to be had here.<br>
3.  Groups that have been trained also train to zone<br>
4.  You end up zoning back and forth<br>
5.  When you finally get finished you attempt to return to camp only to find the mobs still returning to camp you aggro and run to zone and return to point 1.  <br>
<br>
The way that it should be done:  <br>
<br>
1.  Die on the spot, at least you will be less likely to lose your camp.  Besides which you will prolly have a 96% rezzer with you anyway, do you actually realise how little xp you lose ? <br>
2.  Evac to zone, use em if you gottem<br>
3.  If no evaccer, the casters can hold mobs pretty efficiently whilst the tanks return to zone root or mez.<br>
4.  Tanks/Melee die, casters gate.  It is like a 2 minute run back to PoN/PoD/PoV/PoS/BoT<br>
<br>
People do not actually realise by doing the first option you are probably losing more hunting time and as such getting less xp than what you would with option 2.  <br>
<br>
